pr_body:
This implementation uses `scipy` package, which is already a dependency, as opposed to the proof-of-concept implementation (#548 ) which used another external library.

This implementation contains the basic building blocks for the multitaper periodogram(#361 ) and some utility functions, either directly used from `Powerspectrum `or `Crossspectrum `class, or modified for this specific use case.

This is a part of Google Summer of Code 2021, a report for which can be found [here](https://dhruv9vats.github.io/gsoc-2021/)..

pr_title: Extending the Multitapering concept to unevenly sampled time-series: Multitaper Lomb-Scargle
pr_body:
These additions apply the multitapering concept to signals with uneven temporal sampling in order to estimate their power spectrum density. The Lomb (1976) Scargle (1982) periodogram used to calculate the PSD is rapidly computed using Astropy. 

This method is presented in Springford, Eadie & Thompson (2020).

Adds to #361 and #578, and replaces #583.

The newly added functionality is showcased at the end of [this](https://github.com/dhruv9vats/notebooks/blob/multitaper_periodogram/Multitaper/Multitaper_showcase.ipynb) notebook.

pr_title: Extending the Multitapering concept to unevenly sampled time-series: Multitaper Lomb-Scargle
pr_body:
These additions apply the multitapering concept to signals with uneven temporal sampling in order to estimate their power spectrum density. The Lomb (1976) Scargle (1982) periodogram used to calculate the PSD is rapidly computed using the `[nfft](https://github.com/jakevdp/nfft)` library, as shown by Leroy (2012), using the decomposition of Press & Rybicki (1989).

The normalization and frequency outputs are currently set so as to replicate the result of [Springford, Eadie & Thompson (2020)](https://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.3847/1538-3881/ab7fa1). 

Adds to #361.

pr_body:
This is a proof of concept implementation of the Multitaper Periodogram made by wrapping a `Powerspectrum` like class around the [nitime](http://nipy.org/nitime/examples/multi_taper_spectral_estimation.html) implementation of the same. This hopes to show the viability of integrating the Multitaper Periodogram into Stingray as suggested by #361.

In an attempt to resemble the `Powerspectrum` class, in attributes and methods, most of the code was copied/inspired from `powerspectrum.py`, the notable changes being (in `multitaper.py`):

- The `_multitaper_periodogram` method: The wrapper method calling the `nitime` implementation and accounting for normalization and array length discrepancies.
- A `plot_dB` function: A utility function inspired by the `plot` method in `crossspectrum.py`, as an aid in visualizing the PSD on a logarithmic scale.

This image shows the improvements this method brings over the classical periodogram:
![Multitaper](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/65168627/112647790-e1c0fc80-8e6e-11eb-89ae-6efb25a25dfb.png)

Multitaper algorithm improves both the bais and the variance of the power spectrum estimate.
